# CrowdStrike - Detection Rules & Threat Hunting Queries

This repository contains anonymized CrowdStrike Falcon detection rules and threat hunting queries.  
All sensitive information such as hostnames, domains, and paths has been anonymized for safe public distribution.

---

## 1. Velociraptor Activity Detection  
Detects interactions with Velociraptor binaries or its Tools directory, commonly used for forensic collection or potentially abused by attackers.

```csl
ComputerName=* 
AND TargetFileName="\\Device\\HarddiskVolumeX\\Program Files\\Velociraptor\\Tools\\Velociraptor_Buffer.bin"
OR FileName="Velociraptor.exe"
OR FilePath="\\Device\\HarddiskVolumeX\\Program Files\\Velociraptor\\Tools\\"
| groupBy(@timestamp, ComputerName, UserName, LogonDomain,
          GrandParentBaseFileName, ParentBaseFileName, FileName,
          GrandParentImageFilePath, FilePath, TargetFileName,
          TargetImageFileName, SHA256HashData)
````

***

## 2. Active Directory Authentication Failure Anomalies

Identifies abnormal authentication failures on sensitive infrastructure.

```csl
DomainName="*.workers.dev"
| groupBy([@timestamp, host.hostname, DomainName])
AnonymizedHost01 OR AnonymizedHost02
AND #event_simpleName="ActiveDirectoryAuthenticationFailure"
| groupBy(["@timestamp", "user.name", "DomainName",
           "ComputerName", "RemoteIP", "SourceEndpointAddressIP4"])
| sort(count)
```

***

## 3. DNS Requests to Suspicious Domains

Detects DNS queries to domains associated with malicious activity.

```csl
DomainName="example-malicious1.com"
OR DomainName="example-malicious2.top"
| groupBy(["ComputerName", "#event_simpleName", "@timestamp",
           "DnsRequestCount", "ContextBaseFileName", "DomainName",
           "FirstIP4Record"])
| sort(count)
```

***

## 4. Suspicious Downloads via curl

Detects curl usage or requests to suspicious domains.

```csl
#event_simpleName=ProcessRollup2
| CommandLine=/maliciousdomain\.com/i
OR CommandLine=/curl/i
| groupBy(["ComputerName","UserName","ImageFileName",
           "CommandLine","ParentBaseFileName"])
| sort(count)
```

***

## 5. Attack Chain: cmd → curl → mshta

Detects the typical download-and-execute sequence using curl and mshta.

```csl
#event_simpleName=ProcessRollup2
| CommandLine=/maliciousdomain\.com/i
OR CommandLine=/curl/i
OR CommandLine=/mshta/i
| groupBy(["ComputerName","UserName","ImageFileName",
           "ParentBaseFileName","CommandLine"])
| sort(count)
```

***

## 6. Obfuscated mshta Pattern Detection

Identifies the obfuscated usage of mshta often used to evade simple detection rules.

```csl
#event_simpleName=ProcessRollup2
| CommandLine=/\^?m\^?s\^?h\^?t\^?a/i
OR CommandLine=/curl/i
OR CommandLine=/maliciousdomain\.com/i
| groupBy(["ComputerName","UserName","ImageFileName",
           "ParentBaseFileName","CommandLine"])
| sort(count)
```

***

## 7. Behavioral Correlation: curl / mshta / domain

Correlates multiple suspicious commands to strengthen detection confidence.

```csl
#event_simpleName=ProcessRollup2
| CommandLine=/curl|mshta|maliciousdomain\.com/i
| groupBy(["ComputerName","UserName","ImageFileName",
           "ParentBaseFileName","CommandLine"], function=count())
| sort(count, order=desc)
```

***

## 8. Filtering Out Legitimate Scripts

Removes common legitimate DevOps or system updater activities from detection results.

```csl
#event_simpleName=ProcessRollup2
| ImageFileName=/curl\.exe|mshta\.exe/i
| CommandLine=/http|\.hta|maliciousdomain\.com/i
| ParentBaseFileName=/cmd\.exe|powershell\.exe/i
| groupBy(["ComputerName","UserName","ImageFileName",
           "ParentBaseFileName","CommandLine"], function=count())
| sort(count, order=desc)
```

